            "name": "Miriam Wertheimer (translation)",
            "bio": "Miriam Wertheimer (fl. mid-19th c.) was a pioneering English translator of teḥinot in Birmingham, England, and a direct descendant of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akiba_Israel_Wertheimer\">Akiba Israel Wertheimer</a> (1778–1835) was the first Chief Rabbi of Altona and Schleswig-Holstein. We know very little else about her save that she translated a collection of teḥinot from German into English that was published in 1852. She was a friend of Hester Rothschild who translated another collection of teḥinot and paraliturgical prayers. If you know more about Miriam Wertheimer, please <a href=\"/contact/\">contact us</a>.",
